-- Spain Economy Minister to Present Bank Reform Plan, Efe Reports
-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 2012-01-20T07:11:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/spain-economy-minister-to-present-bank-reform-plan-efe-reports.html
Luis de Guindos,  Spain ’s economy
minister, will present at today’s cabinet meeting a plan to
reorganize the banking system,  Efe  reported, citing unidentified
people in the financial industry who are familiar with the
matter.  The plan includes rules on provisions that will require
banks to put aside about 50 billion euros ($65 billion), the
newswire said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Esteban Duarte in Madrid at 
